<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-07T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="326" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Netherlands/52: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Emmet</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-07T15:00:00-05:00">December
                                    7, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>53. Your No. 88, December 5, 1 p.m. Make formal request as stated in
                            second paragraph, adding that former smuggling bases have gradually been
                            closed and smugglers now compelled to obtain cargoes alcohol in European
                            ports and discharge them on high seas into smuggling vessels; that in
                            order to circumvent this latest move of smugglers and prevent them from
                            getting foothold in Netherlands, we believe it would be mutually
                            desirable if Netherland Government would take action requested, or
                            promise to do so in future if smugglers transfer their operations to
                            Dutch territory.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>